src/client/push-client.js
PushClient
description:
PushClient is a front end library that simplifies adding push to your
site.

name: constructor
description:
Constructs a new PushClient.

If the current browser has a push subscription then it will be
obtained in the constructor and a subscriptionChange event will be
dispatched.

params.name: options
params.description:
Options object should be included if you
 want to define any of the following.

params.name: options.workerUrl
params.description:
Service worker URL to be
 registered that will receive push events.

params.name: options.scope
params.description:
The scope that the Service worker should be
 registered with.

name: subscribe
description:
This method will subscribe a use for push messaging.

If permission isn't granted for push, this method will show the
permissions dialog before attempting to subscribe the user to push.

return.description:
A Promise that
 resolves with a PushSubscription if successful.

name: unsubscribe
description: This method will unsubscribe the user from push on the client side.

return.description:
A Promise that
 resolves once the user is unsubscribed.

name: getRegistration
description: Get the registration of the service worker being used for push.

return.description:
A Promise that
 resolves to either a ServiceWorkerRegistration or to null if none.

name: getSubscription
description:
If the user is currently subscribed for push then the returned promise will
resolve with a PushSubscription object, otherwise it will resolve to null.

This will not display the permission dialog.

return.description:
A Promise that resolves with
 a PushSubscription or null.

name: requestPermission
description:
Will manage requesting permission for push messages, resolving
with the final permission status.

return.description: Permission status of granted, default or denied

name: supported
description: You can use this to decide whether to construct a new PushClient or not.

return.description:
Whether the current browser has everything needed
 to use push messaging.

name: getPermissionState
description:
This method can be used to check if subscribing the user will display
the permission dialog or not.

return.description:
PermistionStatus.state will be
'granted', 'denied' or 'prompt' to reflect the current permission state

src/worker/notification-handler.js
notificationHandler
description:
A handler for push events that shows notifications based on the content of
the payload.

The payload must be a JSON-encoded Object with a `notification` key. The
value of the `notification` property will be used as the NotificationOptions
object passed to showNotification. Additionally, the `title` property of the
notification object will be used as the title.

If there is no notification data in the payload, or if there is no body or
title specified, then no notification will be shown.

params.name: event
params.description: The event that we are handling

params.name: defaults
params.description:
If an option is not provided in the payload then
  the value of the same key in the defaults object will be used instead.

return.description: true if a notification was shown, false otherwise
